race.comment: BRUCEY (1) three-year-old gelding by Unite And Conquer from Roadtoplatinum on debut for the Matt Dale yard. This looks a target race after scoring a solid trial win over 800m at Goulburn. Good draw will assist chances. Go close. FALCON GOLD (2) comes here with fitness on his side and deserves another chance from the low draw. Sped across from the outside gate and failed to go on with it when a fading ninth over 1000m at Wagga last time. Placed here two-starts back and can get the job done. NAVAJO CODE (4) trained locally and can improve sharply in this easier contest. Struggled to see the 1200m out when seventh at this track. Has a host of gear changes and sure to be thereabouts. GAELIC GEM (7) returns without a trial after showing ability in her first campaign. Covered ground in the run with a wilting sixth over 1300m at Goulburn. Placed on debut and finds a winnable contest. PURE MELODY (8) back for her second prep without a trial. Showed enough when last in work. Keep safe.
